invariant socket_extra90.getfqdn_func:
  description: "socket.getfqdn.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') == True — socket.getfqdn is a pure-Python function in Lib/socket.py that returns the fully qualified domain name; its __class__.__name__ is 'function'; no prior socket spec anchors this __eq__ call; first standalone for socket.getfqdn class identity under socketmethcls90"
